    "process_narrative": "1. Raw material intake: iron ore (Bailadila mines) and imported coking coal received via rail and the captive Visakhapatnam Port berth, stacked/reclaimed at the Raw Material Handling Plant. 2. Coke Ovens & By-Product Plant: coking coal carbonized into metallurgical coke; by-product gases (coke oven gas) recovered and reused as plant fuel. 3. Sinter Plant: fine iron ore agglomerated into sinter for improved blast furnace burden permeability. 4. Blast Furnace-1 / Blast Furnace-2: sinter, coke, and flux charged from the top; hot blast air injected; molten hot metal (pig iron) tapped and transported by torpedo ladle car to the Steel Melt Shop. 5. Steel Melt Shop-1 & 2: hot metal charged into LD (oxygen) converters, refined, tapped into ladles, secondary-refined, then continuously cast at Casters 1-6 into blooms (Caster-2 handles a portion of this casting load). 6. Rolling: cast blooms reheated and hot-rolled at the LMMM and Wire Rod Mill into finished TMT bars.",
